[SN]TITLE[SN]
Chile 1-2 Argentina: Lionel Messi returns in win

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Lionel Messi inspired Argentina to a 2-1 win over Chile in South American qualifying for the 2018 World Cup.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Barcelona forward, who missed the first four games of the campaign with a knee injury, laid on the 24th-minute winner for defender Gabriel Mercado.
Felipe Gutierrez had put Chile ahead before Paris St-Germain winger Angel Di Maria equalised in Santiago.
Argentina, beaten finalists in 2014, are fourth in the 10-team group with the top four qualifying automatically.
Second-placed Uruguay play Brazil, who are fifth, in Recife on Friday, in Luis Suarez's first competitive international since biting Giorgio Chiellini at the 2014 World Cup.
